The first thing happening once you click import is that a GET request to /rest/studio/svnimport/1.0/importer/unknownusers is issued. This unzips the file, pipes it through grep and checks if the svn authors are also studio users. The response contains an array of svn authors not being studio users. The svnimport.checkUnknownUsers in the svnimport.js issued that request, and it will call svnimport.doImportFile(fileName) on success (which will issue the POST request which triggers the import). 

The problem with large files is that this call can lead to a client-side timeout, in which case the 

{code}
            error: function(xhr, status, error) {

                svnimport.glass(false, null);

                svnimport.showErrorBox(svnimport.getXhrErrorResponse(xhr), function() {
                    svnimport.initialGetStatus();
                });
            }
{code}

in line 267-274 (rev. 116923) of the svnimport.js gets called. The error variable is just "timeout", the actual error box will contain no message. The error box is shown in FF but not in Chrome. 

A rather crappy fix would be to just increase the [timeout|http://api.jquery.com/jQuery.ajax/], my suggestion would be to directly return and query periodically for the result like it is done with the actual import. 

This bug can be worked around by just issueing the POST manually (e.g. with Poster on FF), which would be sth. like <myjira>/rest/studio/svnimport/1.0/importer?file=<myimportfile>. Then you would just refresh <myjira>/secure/admin/SvnImporter.jspa page and overview the import.

ConfluenceInitialData references the {{setupSidManager}} like so:

{code}
ConfluenceSidManager setupSidManager = (ConfluenceSidManager) BootstrapUtils.getBootstrapContext().getBean("setupSidManager");
{code}

This changed names in Confluence 4.0 to {{bootstrapSidManager}} - I propose changing the by-name referencing to reference by the class such as:

{code}
ConfluenceSidManager setupSidManager = (ConfluenceSidManager) BeanFactoryUtils.beanOfType(BootstrapUtils.getBootstrapContext(), ConfluenceSidManager.class);
{code}

A simular method should be used in locations that use {{ContainerManager.getComponent("blah");}}. Making this change should insulate the JST setup data from future bean name changes in Confluence.

